{{Lunisolar October}} '''October 4''' is the 4th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=Kannazuki|1=Kannazuki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4 ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|632|ja|632nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The first {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} mission returns to Japan. * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (Julian {{ill|698|ja|698th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 12|ja|11月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Yakushi-ji|ja|薬師寺|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , founded by the will of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , is established in {{ill|Fujiwara-kyō|ja|藤原京|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Ōan (Japan)|ja|応安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5 / {{ill|Bunchū (Japan)|ja|文中|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (Julian {{ill|1372|ja|1372nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Southern Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} changes the era name from {{ill|Kenchoku|ja|建徳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to Bunchū. * {{ill|Hōei (Japan)|ja|宝永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1707|ja|1707th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 28|ja|10月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} *. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|ja|富岡製糸場|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} begins operations.
