raft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} *. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|ja|富岡製糸場|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} begins operations.
== Births == * {{ill|Keichō (era)|ja|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12 (Gregorian {{ill|1607|ja|1607th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 23|ja|11月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Masako|ja|徳川和子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (known as {{ill|Tōfukumon-in|ja|東福門院|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ), consort of {{ill|Emperor Go-Mizunoo|ja|後水尾天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and daughter of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|ja|徳川秀忠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (+ {{ill|1678|ja|1678th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). == Deaths ==
