* {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇}}  4 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}}  {{ill|632|ja|632nd year}}  {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日}} ) – The first {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)}}  mission returns to Japan.
* {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇}}  2 (Julian {{ill|698|ja|698th year}}  {{ill|November 12|ja|11月12日}} ) – {{ill|Yakushi-ji|ja|薬師寺}} , founded by the will of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu}} , is established in {{ill|Fujiwara-kyō|ja|藤原京}} .
* {{ill|Ōan (Japan)|ja|応安|1=Ōan|lt=Ōan era}}  5 / {{ill|Bunchū (Japan)|ja|文中}}  1 (Julian {{ill|1372|ja|1372nd year}}  {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日}} ) – The {{ill|Southern Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)}}  changes the era name from {{ill|Kenchoku|ja|建徳}}  to Bunchū.
* {{ill|Hōei (Japan)|ja|宝永}}  4 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}}  {{ill|1707|ja|1707th year}}  {{ill|October 28|ja|10月28日}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国}}  and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国}}  coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes.
* {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保}}  1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year}}  {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石}}  begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記}} *.
