{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月初四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 4일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 4''' is the 4th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 4 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|632|ja|632nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – The first {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} mission returns to Japan. * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 2 (Julian {{ill|698|ja|698th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 12|ja|11月12日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Yakushi-ji|ja|薬師寺|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , founded by the will of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , is established in {{ill|Fujiwara-kyō|ja|藤原京|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} . * {{ill|Ōan (Japan)|ja|応安|1=Ōan|lt=Ōan era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 5 / {{ill|Bunchū (Japan)|ja|文中|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 (Julian {{ill|1372|ja|1372nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Southern Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} changes the era name from {{ill|Kenchoku|ja|建徳|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to Bunchū. * {{ill|Hōei (Japan)|ja|宝永|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 4 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|1707|ja|1707th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 28|ja|10月28日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|ja|富岡製糸場|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} begins operations.
== Births == * {{ill|Keichō (era)|ja|Keichō|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 12 (Gregorian {{ill|1607|ja|1607th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 23|ja|11月23日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Masako|ja|徳川和子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (known as {{ill|Tōfukumon-in|ja|東福門院|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ), consort of {{ill|Emperor Go-Mizunoo|ja|後水尾天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and daughter of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|ja|徳川秀忠|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (+ {{ill|1678|ja|1678th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ). == Deaths ==
