)|ja|南朝 (日本)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Southern Court (Japan)|qq=}} changes the era name from {{ill|Kenchoku|ja|建徳|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenchoku|qq=}} to Bunchū. * {{ill|Hōei (Japan)|ja|宝永|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei (Japan)|qq=}} 4 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} {{ill|1707|ja|1707th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1707|qq=}} {{ill|October 28|ja|10月28日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October 28|qq=}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōtōmi Province|qq=}} and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii Province|qq=}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei earthquake|qq=}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōhō (era)|qq=}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1716|qq=}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 17|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arai Hakuseki|qq=}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oridataku Shiba no Ki|qq=}} *. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1872|qq=}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 4|qq=}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|ja|富岡製糸場|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomioka Silk Mill|qq=}} begins operations.
