== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Jomei|ja|舒明天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Jomei|qq=}} 4 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|qq=}} {{ill|632|ja|632nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/632|qq=}} {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 21|qq=}} ) – The first {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kentōshi|qq=}} mission returns to Japan. * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Monmu|qq=}} 2 (Julian {{ill|698|ja|698th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/698|qq=}} {{ill|November 12|ja|11月12日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 12|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Yakushi-ji|ja|薬師寺|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushi-ji|qq=}} , founded by the will of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} , is established in {{ill|Fujiwara-kyō|ja|藤原京|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara-kyō|qq=}} . * {{ill|Ōan (Japan)|ja|応安|1=Ōan|lt=Ōan era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōan (Japan)|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōan|qq=}} 5 / {{ill|Bunchū (Japan)|ja|文中|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunchū (Japan)|qq=}} 1 (Julian {{ill|1372|ja|1372nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1372|qq=}} {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October 30|qq=}} ) – The {{ill|Southern Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Southern Court (Japan)|qq=}} changes the era name from {{ill|Kenchoku|ja|建徳|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenchoku|qq=}} to Bunchū. * {{ill|Hōei (Japan)|ja|宝永|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei (Japan)|qq=}} 4 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} {{ill|1707|ja|1707th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1707|qq=}} {{ill|October 28|ja|10月28日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October 28|qq=}} ) – A major earthquake strikes {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōtōmi Province|qq=}} and the {{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii Province|qq=}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei earthquake|qq=}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō (era)|ja|享保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōhō (era)|qq=}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|ja|1716th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1716|qq=}} {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 17|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|ja|新井白石|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arai Hakuseki|qq=}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oridataku Shiba no Ki|ja|折たく柴の記|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oridataku Shiba no Ki|qq=}} *. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1872|qq=}} {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 4|qq=}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|ja|富岡製糸場|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomioka Silk Mill|qq=}} begins operations.
== Births == * {{ill|Keichō (era)|ja|Keichō|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō (era)|qq=}} 12 (Gregorian {{ill|1607|ja|1607th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1607|qq=}} {{ill|November 23|ja|11月23日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November 23|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Masako|ja|徳川和子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Masako|qq=}} (known as {{ill|Tōfukumon-in|ja|東福門院|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōfukumon-in|qq=}} ), consort of {{ill|Emperor Go-Mizunoo|ja|後水尾天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Mizunoo|qq=}} and daughter of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|ja|徳川秀忠|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Hidetada|qq=}} (+ {{ill|1678|ja|1678th year|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1678|qq=}} ). == Deaths ==
