{{Not to be confused with|October 4|qq=October 4}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月初四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 4일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 4''' is the 4th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}} .
== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Jomei|Emperor Jomei]] 4 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:632|632]] [[:en:November 21|November 21]] ) – The first {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kentōshi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} mission returns to Japan. * [[:en:Emperor Monmu|Emperor Monmu]] 2 (Julian [[:en:698|698]] [[:en:November 12|November 12]] ) – [[:en:Yakushi-ji|Yakushi-ji]] , founded by the will of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , is established in [[:en:Fujiwara-kyō|Fujiwara-kyō]] . * [[:en:Ōan|Ōan era]] 5 / [[:en:Bunchū|Bunchū (Japan)]] 1 (Julian [[:en:1372|1372]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ) – The [[:en:Southern Court|Southern Court (Japan)]] changes the era name from [[:en:Kentoku|Kenchoku]] to Bunchū. * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei (Japan)]] 4 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1707|1707]] [[:en:October 28|October 28]] ) – A major earthquake strikes [[:en:Tōtōmi Province|Tōtōmi Province]] and the [[:en:Kii Province|Kii Province]] coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei earthquake|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō (era)]] 1 (Gregorian [[:en:1716|1716]] [[:en:November 17|November 17]] ) – [[:en:Arai Hakuseki|Arai Hakuseki]] begins writing his autobiography, *[[:en:Oritaku Shiba no Ki|Oridataku Shiba no Ki]] *. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5 (Gregorian [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:November 4|November 4]] ) – The government-run [[:en:Tomioka Silk Mill|Tomioka Silk Mill]] begins operations.
== Births == * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 12 (Gregorian [[:en:1607|1607]] [[:en:November 23|November 23]] ) – [[:en:Tokugawa Masako|Tokugawa Masako]] (known as {{ill|Tōfukumon-in|ja|東福門院|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōfukumon-in|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 徳川和子}} ), consort of [[:en:Emperor Go-Mizunoo|Emperor Go-Mizunoo]] and daughter of [[:en:Tokugawa Hidetada|Tokugawa Hidetada]] (+ [[:en:1678|1678]] ). == Deaths ==
