{ill|Kii Province|en|Kii Province|WD=Q864053|lt=Kii Province|1=Kii Province}} coast, known as the {{ill|Hōei earthquake|ja|宝永の大Earthquake|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei earthquake|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , with a magnitude of 8.4, making it one of Japan’s largest recorded earthquakes. * {{ill|Kyōhō|en|Kyōhō|WD=Q1145048|lt=Kyōhō (era)|1=Kyōhō}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1716|en|1716|WD=Q6892|lt=1716|1=1716}} {{ill|November 17|en|November 17|WD=Q3028|lt=November 17|1=November 17}} ) – {{ill|Arai Hakuseki|en|Arai Hakuseki|WD=Q467616|lt=Arai Hakuseki|1=Arai Hakuseki}} begins writing his autobiography, *{{ill|Oritaku Shiba no Ki|en|Oritaku Shiba no Ki|WD=Q3007804|lt=Oridataku Shiba no Ki|1=Oritaku Shiba no Ki}} *. * {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} {{ill|November 4|en|November 4|WD=Q2994|lt=November 4|1=November 4}} ) – The government-run {{ill|Tomioka Silk Mill|en|Tomioka Silk Mill|WD=Q7818931|lt=Tomioka Silk Mill|1=Tomioka Silk Mill}} begins operations.
== Births == * {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|WD=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 12 (Gregorian {{ill|1607|en|1607|WD=Q6756|lt=1607|1=1607}} {{ill|November 23|en|November 23|WD=Q3021|lt=November 23|1=November 23}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Masako|en|Tokugawa Masako|WD=Q911334|lt=Tokugawa Masako|1=Tokugawa Masako}} (known as {{ill|Tōfukumon-in|ja|東福門院|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōfukumon-in|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 徳川和子|1=Tokugawa Masako|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q911334}} ), consort of {{ill|Emperor Go-Mizunoo|en|Emperor Go-Mizunoo|WD=Q320229|lt=Emperor Go-Mizunoo|1=Emperor Go-Mizunoo}} and daughter of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|en|Tokugawa Hidetada|WD=Q314464|lt=Tokugawa Hidetada|1=Tokugawa Hidetada}} (+ {{ill|1678|en|1678|WD=Q7634|lt=1678|1=1678}} ). == Deaths ==
